</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here are three ways to become a billionaire. O=
ne is you create some good or service, you sell it for more than it costs y=
ou to produce it, and you keep doing that until you have a billion dollars.=
 Call this a=C2=A0<em>cash billionaire</em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another is you create some good or service, yo=
u sell it for more than it costs you to produce it, and you keep doing that=
 until you are making, like, $100 million a year. Then you do a discounted =
cash flow analysis and say =E2=80=9Cwell, it=E2=80=99s $100 million a year,=
 figure it grows at 8% per year for the next 20 years, discount that back t=
o today at a 15% discount rate and you get a present value of=C2=A0more tha=
n a billion dollars.=E2=80=9D You own a stream of future cash flows worth $=
1 billion, which makes you a billionaire. This is a fairly common way for a=
 business owner to become a billionaire; it has also become possible for ce=
lebrities, and we have talked about it in relation to <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33314957.258406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjYvbXVzay13aWxsLWJ1eS10d2l0dG=
VyLWF0LXRoZS1sYXN0LW1pbnV0ZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA5MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVka=
XVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBh=
aWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3c4ab2b2" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Ye</a> (Kan=
ye West) and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33314=
957.258406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMt=
MTAtMzAvdHdvLXNpZ21hLWhhZC1hLXJvZ3VlLWNhbGlicmF0b3I_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwOTIzX01=
PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm=
09MjMxMTA5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2f592b6=
2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  Taylor Swift</a>. Call this a=C2=A0<em>discounted cash flow =
billionaire</em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are that sort of billionaire, you can p=
robably=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33314=
957.258406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEt=
MDctMjIvcHJpdmF0ZS1lcXVpdHktZmlybS1nb3QtcmljaC1tYWtpbmctcHJpdmF0ZS1lcXVpdHk=
tZmlybXMtcmljaD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA5MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJn=
V0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c=
3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBac594667" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"><em>convert=C2=A0</em>it=
 into cash</a>, or some of it anyway. You can take your company public and =
sell your stock; you can sell your music catalogue to a private equity firm=
. You don=E2=80=99t have to:=C2=A0Bloomberg has <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33314957.258406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9ncmFwaGljcy8yMDIzLXRheWxvci1zd2lmdC1uZXQtd29ydGgtYmlsbGlvbmFpcmUvP2Nt=
cGlkPUJCRDExMDkyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXd=
zbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEwOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cBb6303d09" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">  anointed Taylor Swift a billionaire</a> w=
ithout her selling her catalogue (or having a billion dollars). But if you =
don=E2=80=99t convert to cash, your billionaire status is=C2=A0at risk. Tho=
se recurring cash flows are not certain in all future states of the world. =
Ye=E2=80=99s stream of nine-digit cash flows was abruptly cut off due to ba=
d tweets, so he stopped being a billionaire.=C2=A0It=E2=80=99s not that he =
had a billion dollars in the bank and someone took it away from him; it=E2=
=80=99s that he had expected future cash flows worth a billion dollars, and=
 then expectations changed. Sam Bankman-Fried was worth tens of billions of=
 dollars due to the large and growing cash flows of the crypto exchange he =
owned, and then he wasn=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This shades into the third way to become a bil=
lionaire. Call it a=C2=A0<em>probabilistic=C2=A0</em>billionaire.<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0You create some company that does a thing, or hopes to, and even =
before it makes any money you say, well, this company has a 1% chance of be=
ing worth $1 trillion, so its expected value, today, is $10 billion.<a clas=
s=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent =
!important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> Anyone can=C2=A0<em>say=C2=A0</em>that =E2=80=94 you=C2=A0can say =E2=
=80=9CI have a 1% chance of discovering teleportation, which is probably a =
$1 trillion business, so I=E2=80=99m worth $10 billion today=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0but that won=E2=80=99t get you on anyone=E2=80=99s list of bill=
ionaires.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand if you convince someone=C2=
=A0<em>else=C2=A0</em>that you have a 1% chance at doing a trillion-dollar =
thing, and=C2=A0<em>that person=C2=A0</em>has a lot of money, and she gives=
 you $1 billion for a 10% stake in your company, then you really are a bill=
ionaire. Because you have a billion dollars in the bank.=C2=A0But that is n=
ot a strict requirement: If she gives you $100 million for a 1% stake in yo=
ur company, you have $100 million in the bank, but also a mark-to-market va=
luation that says your remaining 99% stake is worth $9.9 billion. That=C2=
=A0<em>might=C2=A0</em>get you on a list of billionaires. If you sell five =
1% stakes to reputable venture capital=C2=A0firms for $100 million each, yo=
u=E2=80=99re almost certainly=C2=A0on all the lists.<a class=3D"footnote-in=
dex" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; disp=
lay: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course eventually you will either succeed (=
with 1% probability) or fail (99%) at creating a trillion-dollar company.=
=C2=A0If time goes by and you do not discover teleportation and you get bor=
ed and go back to your day job, then (let us assume) your probability of ma=
king $1 trillion goes to zero, and you are no longer a billionaire.<em> Unl=
ess you already converted some of your stake to cash</em>. If you convinced=
 someone to give you a billion dollars for a 10% stake in your company with=
 a 1% chance at a trillion-dollar idea, and then the company goes to zero, =
then:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">
<em>You</em> have a billion dollars, and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">
<em>She</em> has lost a billion dollars.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s it. The trillion dollars is gon=
e, though it was never there; the true ex ante odds of you making a trillio=
n dollars are essentially unknowable, but the ex post result is that you di=
dn=E2=80=99t.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background=
-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But you thought about it, and your billion-dollar backer thought =
about it, and your shared belief led to=C2=A0a transfer of $1 billion from =
her bank account to your bank account, and that is the only thing that has =
happened in objective reality. The teleportation never happened, the trilli=
on-dollar company never happened, but she really did write you that check a=
nd you really did cash it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33314957.258406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDgvd2V3b3JrLWlzLWJhbmtydXB0LWJ1dC1hZ=
GFtLW5ldW1hbm4taXMtc3RpbGwtYS1iaWxsaW9uYWlyZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA5MjNfTU9ORVlT=
VFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzE=
xMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbaab3349" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;">  Bloomberg's Tom Maloney on Adam Neumann</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">WeWork Inc. never figured out how to make mone=
y. Adam Neumann sure did.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The office-leasing business declared bankruptc=
y this week, two years after finally going public minus its infamous co-fou=
nder. It has $19 billion of liabilities and $15 billion of assets. Longtime=
 investors, including Softbank Group Corp. and the Vision Fund, will add to=
 the enormous losses they=E2=80=99ve already taken on the venture.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt has been challenging for me to wat=
ch from the sidelines as WeWork has failed to take advantage of a product t=
hat is more relevant today than ever before,=E2=80=9D Neumann, 44, said in =
a statement.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But a part of Neumann might be thankful he was=
 forced out in 2019 following the company=E2=80=99s disastrous first attemp=
t at an initial public offering. While battering his reputation, the exit l=
eft him with plenty of liquidity, and he=E2=80=99s still worth $1.7 billion=
, according to the Bloomberg Billionaires Index.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/33314957.258406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMTAtMjMvaG93LWRvLXlvdS1saWtlLXdlLW5vdz9jbXBpZD1CQkQ=
xMTA5MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlci=
Z1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cBa495d8f4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  discussed</a> this <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/33314957.258406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS=
9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDcvYnJpZGdld2F0ZXItaGFkLWJlbGlldmFiaWxpd=
HktaXNzdWVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMDkyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRt=
X3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEwOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHV=
mZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6453d68c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  before</a>. My view is: Oh=
 yes! Adam Neumann really did figure out how to make money. He figured out =
maybe the best and funniest=C2=A0way anyone has ever made money in the hist=
ory of capitalism, which is =E2=80=9Cact crazy around Masayoshi Son until m=
oney spews out of him.=E2=80=9D Figuring out how to rent out office space f=
